{
  "texts": [
    "The market for the Internet of Things (IoT) is growing rapidly.",
    "It is estimated to increase from 370.5 billion in 2021 to 1.3 trillion by 2026, with a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 27.6% (Rangasamy et al. 2023).",
    "In particular, the use of IoT applications in smart wearables, smart cities, smart homes, and building automation is expected to grow from 137.1 billion in 2021 to 438.2 billion by 2026, at a CAGR of 26.2% (Chataut and Phoummalayvane 2023).",
    "This growth is driven by the increasing connectivity of devices to the internet, enabling a wide range of applications across industries such as healthcare and agriculture (Chataut and Phoummalayvane 2023).",
    "The emergence of 5G, as well as upcoming 6G and 7G technologies, will further enhance the connectivity and capabilities of IoT devices, leading to a transformative impact on our interaction with technology and the world around us (Bhatia et al. 2023)."
  ]
}